SeekableXPathNavigator Class

In this Article

Provides read-only, random access to data contained in XML documents and enables efficient querying for specified nodes.

Remarks

The SOAP messages passed between parts of the Windows Communication Foundation (WCF) system are handled by various components of the system that must inspect these messages to determine what actions to take in processing them. The XPath engine is a component that queries messages for this purpose and it requires a navigator to read SOAP messages and other XML documents. A navigator provides a cursor that moves from node to node tracking where the XML document is actually being read.

The XPath engine works with a SeekableXPathNavigator, which extends the XPathNavigator class by adding a CurrentPosition property. This property allows positions within the XML document to be saved and loaded quickly without having to clone the navigator, an expensive memory allocation that the XPathNavigator requires for such an operation. The XPath engine must frequently record the position of the cursor in the course of executing queries on XML documents, so the SeekableXPathNavigator provides an important optimization for message processing.

Note that the value of the CurrentPosition property is implementation-specific and may not map to node position or character position. Its value is only meaningful to the SeekableXPathNavigator implementation (and instance) that supplied it.

  • SeekableXPathNavigator()

    protected SeekableXPathNavigator ();

Properties

  • CurrentPosition

    When overridden in a derived class, gets or sets a value associated with the node in the data where the XPath navigator is positioned.

    public abstract long CurrentPosition { get; set; }

    Property Value

    • Int64

      A value that is associated with the navigatorâ€™s current position.

    Remarks

    The set operation moves the navigator to the position associated with the value specified. The get operation returns a value associated with the current position of the navigator.

Methods

  • ComparePosition(Int64,Int64)

    When overridden in a derived class, returns a value that describes the document order of the two specified positions.

    public abstract System.Xml.XmlNodeOrder ComparePosition (long firstPosition, long secondPosition);

    Parameters

    • firstPosition
      Int64

      The first position in the comparison.

    • secondPosition
      Int64

      The second position in the comparison.

    Returns

    • XmlNodeOrder

      One of the XmlNodeOrder values that describes the relation of firstPosition to secondPosition in the document.

    Exceptions

    • ArgumentException

      firstPosition or secondPosition is not valid.

  • GetLocalName(Int64)

    When overridden in a derived class, returns the local name of the node at the position specified.

    public abstract string GetLocalName (long nodePosition);

    Parameters

    • nodePosition
      Int64

      The position of the node whose local name is being retrieved.

    Returns

    • String

      The local name of the node at the specified position. String is returned if the node does not have a local name, for example if the current position references a text node.

    Exceptions

    • ArgumentException

      nodePosition is invalid.

  • GetName(Int64)

    When overridden in a derived class, returns the name of the node at the specified position.

    public abstract string GetName (long nodePosition);

    Parameters

    • nodePosition
      Int64

      The position of the node whose name is being retrieved.

    Returns

    • String

      The name of the node at nodePosition. String is returned if the node does not have a name.

    Exceptions

    • ArgumentException

      nodePosition is invalid.

    Remarks

    The name is the name of the XML element at nodePosition and typically includes a namespace prefix.

  • GetNamespace(Int64)

    When overridden in a derived class, returns the namespace of the node at the specified position.

    public abstract string GetNamespace (long nodePosition);

    Parameters

    • nodePosition
      Int64

      The position of the node whose namespace is being retrieved.

    Returns

    • String

      The namespace of the node at nodePosition. String is returned if the node does not have a namespace.

    Exceptions

    • ArgumentException

      nodePosition is invalid.

  • GetNodeType(Int64)

    When overridden in a derived class, returns the type of the node at the specified position.

    public abstract System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType GetNodeType (long nodePosition);

    Parameters

    • nodePosition
      Int64

      The position of the node whose node type is being retrieved.

    Returns

    • XPathNodeType

      One of the XPathNodeType values that indicate the type of the XML node.

    Exceptions

    • ArgumentException

      nodePosition is invalid.

  • GetValue(Int64)

    When overridden in a derived class, returns the text value of the node at the specified position.

    public abstract string GetValue (long nodePosition);

    Parameters

    • nodePosition
      Int64

      The position of the node whose text value is being retrieved.

    Returns

    • String

      The text value of the node at nodePosition. String is returned if the node does not have a text value.

    Exceptions

    • ArgumentException

      nodePosition is invalid.

    Remarks

    For elements, this method returns the concatenation of all text descendents of the node at the specified position, similar to the InnerText property.
